name: ƒåesk√° spo≈ôitelna, a.s. - poboƒçka
review_text: The other negative reviews of this bank are right on target. On my first day visiting Prague, I waited in line with a simple and modest request: to change two 100 krona bills into 20 krona coins. A mere 10 coins total! The unsmiling cashier refused with a blunt "no." In disbelief, I asked again. Another "no" with an attitude of great annoyance, as if I were seeking a terrible imposition, instead of asking for a basic service of the type banks are in business to provide! He eventually, very grudgingly, gave me four 50 krona coins (20 krona are far more convenient for WCs, machines, etc). I had earlier asked a currency exchange office to change bills for coins, but the clerk impatiently said "We are not a bank," yet was actually nice enough to take pity on me and change one bill! But some banks apparently also take the attitude that "We are not a bank!" I urge my Czech and non-Czech friends: take your business elsewhere!
